From hpages at fredhutch.org  Tue Jul 12 12:00:23 2016
From: hpages at fredhutch.org (=?UTF-8?B?SGVydsOpIFBhZ8Oocw==?=)
Date: Tue, 12 Jul 2016 03:00:23 -0700
Subject: [Bioc-devel] 48-hour build cycle for devel packages
Message-ID: <5784BFB7.6000606@fredhutch.org>

Developers,

We're temporarily switching to a 48-hour (instead of 24-hour) build
cycle for devel packages. The new schedule is as follow:

   1) Builds will start on Saturdays, Mondays, and Wednesdays at 7:15 pm
      (Seattle time) every week.

   2) Build reports will be generated about 32 hours later i.e. on
      Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays around 3 am (Seattle time)
      every week.

We started using this new schedule yesterday (Monday) so if everything
goes as expected we should get an updated build report here

   https://bioconductor.org/checkResults/3.4/bioc-LATEST/

tomorrow (Wednesday) around 3 am Seattle time. It should include
results for moscato1 (Windows).

Hopefully we will be able to switch back to a 24-hour cycle (aka
"nightly builds") soon when we replace moscato1 with a more powerful
machine.

Cheers,
H.

